{
  "texts": [
    "This method partitions observations into distinct clusters based on similar behaviours or patterns.",
    "As a result, K-means clustering supports organising large sets of SR datasets, e.g.",
    "abstracts, into clusters based on similarities in their text content.",
    "This grouping helps identify patterns or themes common to certain clusters, which can indicate relevance to the research questions or criteria of the SR.",
    "While K-Means is computationally efficient, determining the optimal number of clusters remains challenging Ahmed et al. (2020)."
  ]
}